item.title: CVE-2021-29695|2024-09-16T20:59:08.689Z -- ibm -- 8335-gtb
item.description: IBM Host firmware for LC-class Systems could allow a remote attacker to traverse directories on the system. An attacker could send a specially-crafted URL request that would allow them to delete arbitrary files on the system. IBM X-Force ID: 200558.

item.title: CVE-2020-4839|2024-09-16T20:31:49.598Z -- ibm -- 8335-gtb
item.description: IBM Host firmware for LC-class Systems is vulnerable to a stack based buffer overflow, caused by improper bounds checking. A remote privileged attacker could exploit this vulnerability and cause a denial of service. IBM X-Force ID: 190037.
